The paper deals with steganography, which is a subfield of computer security (cs.CR). The algorithm proposed in the paper involves manipulating pixels in an image, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also mentions the use of modulus arithmetic, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the algorithm using peak signal-to-noise ratio, which is a metric commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG).
